What is the Idaho Quality Schools Consortium?
<font></td></table>

The Idaho Quality Schools Consortium was founded in 1997 as one of several initiatives associated with the J.A. and Kathryn Albertson Foundation designed to positively impact Idaho's public schools.  The Consortium's mission is to provide Idaho schools with the training and support needed to implement Quality Management theory and processes as a means of ensuring a high quality education for every student.  The Consortium thus helps schools and school districts create and manage effective change that results in the continuous improvement of student learning.
<p>
The Consortium is affiliated with the University of Idaho.  Guided by a Steering Committe representing a cross section of Idaho's education community, a QSC Director plans and implements consortium strategies for project success.  Consortium members consist of a revolving group of school districts committed to creating continuous improvement in their schools.
<p>

