What is meant by the term Quality Management?
<font></td></table>

Quality Management, as used by QSC, refers to the application to education systems of those principles and practices that have  revolutionized America's business world during the past twenty-five years.  An increasing number of schools are using Quality Management to change school climates and increase student learning.
<p>
The Quality Management approach involves an emphasis on customer satisfaction, a planned approach to change, systems thinking, leadership and learning, and collaboration and community.  Quality Management includes a set of beliefs and operating principles as well as specific tools helpful in identifying systemic problems and assessing improvement.
<p>
Schools throughout the United States are applying Quality Management practices in individual classrooms, entire schools and school districts.  Many business corporations are assisting in this effort.  Quality Management complements vision-driven strategic planning and the activities now required in new procedures for school accreditation.
<p>

