How does the Quality Schools Consortium pursue its mission?
<font></td></table>

The QSC provides training, coaching and consultation in a three-stage process customized to the specific needs of each member district:
<dl>
<dt><b>Awareness and Consensus</b>
<dd>QSC personnel first visit with school and school district administrative staff or leadership teams to explain the QSC program in detail. If the district is then interested in pursuing a relationship with the QSC, we next provide a one-half or one-day introduction to Quality Management, change , and leadership to the school personnel who would be involved were the school district to join the Consortium.  We also welcome the opportunity to present such information to school boards and other community members.  A decision to proceed further is based upon some form of staff consensus.  While only school districts are actual Consortium members, the QSC can serve one or more schools within a member district.
<dt><b>Training and Coaching</b>
<dd>Working cooperatively with district personnel, the QSC staff plans a customized training program that will meet the needs of the involved educators and which contains critical elements necessary for success.  Training will include intensive workshops and on-site coaching and consultation.  The training cycle typically requires from one to two years to complete.
<dt><b>Planning and Support</b>
<dd>In the final state of the training process, the QSC assists the district in developing a multi-year plan for continuous improvement.  The QSC may also assist with issues related to future funding assistance from members of the Idaho business community.
<dt><b>Quality Leadership Institute</b>
<dd>In the interest of building in-state capacity for catalyzing educational change and continuous improvement, the QSC also operates a Quality Leadership Institute designed to identify, train, inspire and support a cadre of leaders in Idaho education.  The Institute focuses on individuals from both K-12 public schools and schools of education within Idaho's public colleges and universities.
</dl>


